1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,930
Action feeds and strengthens confidence.
2
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:06,130
Inaction, in all forms, feeds fear.
3
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:08,529
To fight fear, act.
4
00:00:08,719 --> 00:00:12,930
To increase fear, wait, put off, postpone.
5
00:00:14,240 --> 00:00:20,370
Once I heard a young paratrooper instructor explain, the jump really isn't so bad.
6
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:23,170
It's the waiting to jump that gets a fellow.
7
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:28,370
On the trip to the jump site, I always try to make the time pass quickly for the men.
8
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:34,290
It's happened more than once that a trainee thought too much about what may happen and panicked.
9
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:39,009
If we can't get him to jump the next trip, he's through as a paratrooper.
10
00:00:39,120 --> 00:00:45,009
Instead of gaining confidence, the longer he postpones the jump, the more scared he gets.
11
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:48,690
Waiting even makes the experts nervous.
12
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:57,969
Time magazine reported that Edward R. Murrow, the nation's top newscaster, perspires and is on edge just before he telecasts.
13
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:01,330
But once he's in action, fear disappears.
14
00:01:01,680 --> 00:01:05,249
Many veteran actors experience the same sensation.
15
00:01:05,520 --> 00:01:09,330
They agree that the only cure for stage fright is action.
16
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:15,330
Getting right out there before the audience is the cure for dread, worry, fear.
17
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:23,090
Action Cures Fear One evening, we were visiting in a friend's home when their five-year-old boy,
18
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:26,529
who had been put to bed thirty minutes before, cried out.
19
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:36,290
The youngster had been overstimulated by a science fiction film and was afraid the little green monsters were going to enter his room and kidnap him.
20
00:01:36,719 --> 00:01:41,090
I was intrigued by the way the boy's father relieved the lad's worry.
21
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:46,370
He didn't say, don't worry son, nothing is going to get you, go back to sleep.
22
00:01:46,719 --> 00:01:49,249
Instead, he took positive action.
23
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:54,769
He made quite a show for the boy by inspecting the windows to be sure they were tight.
24
00:01:55,040 --> 00:02:00,690
Then he picked up one of the boy's plastic guns and put it on a table beside his bed and said,
25
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:04,130
Billy, here's a gun for you just in case.
26
00:02:04,479 --> 00:02:07,249
The little fellow had a look of complete relief.
27
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:10,449
Four minutes later, he was fast asleep.
28
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:19,570
Many physicians give neutral, harmless medication to people who insist they've got to have something to make them sleep.
29
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:26,690
To lots of folks, the act of swallowing a pill, even though unknown to them the pill has no medication,
30
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:28,370
makes them feel better.
31
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:37,570
It's perfectly natural to experience fear in one of many forms, but the usual methods of combating it simply don't work.
32
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:45,410
I've been with many salesmen who tried to cure fear, which creeps up on even the most experienced of them at times,
33
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:49,650
by going around the block a few times or drinking extra coffee.
34
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:52,050
But these things don't get results.
35
00:02:52,400 --> 00:03:00,610
The way to combat that kind of fear, yes, any kind of fear, yes, any kind of fear, is action.
36
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,810
Dread making a certain phone call?
37
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,209
Make it, and dread disappears.
38
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:10,050
Put it off, and it will get harder and harder to make.
39
00:03:10,479 --> 00:03:13,170
Dread going to a doctor for a checkup?
40
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:15,570
Go, and your worry vanishes.
41
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:21,489
Chances are nothing serious is wrong with you, and if there is, you know where you stand.
42
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:28,850
Put off that checkup, and you feed your fear until it may grow so strong that you actually are sick.
43
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:32,529
Dread discussing a problem with your superior?
44
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:36,449
Discuss it and discover how those worries are conquered.
45
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:38,370
Build confidence.
46
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:41,249
Destroy fear through action.
